Love these cartoons from my childhood! I'm glad I found them on DVD! They're a lot of fun - we love the musical Sneetches and Green Eggs and Ham. The Zax cartoon is still...weird...and not as fun. But the other two more than make up for it!
I mean come on, who doesn't love Green Eggs and Ham?
My daughter was excited to get Green Eggs and Ham for her daughter as she heard it so often when she was little; then she heard it frequently when her siblings were having it read for them.

This movie is great! I am always on the lookout for a children/s dvd that is good, but is not a full length "Disney" feature. When the kids need entertainment, but don't have two hours to kill for instance.  This movie fills the bill perfectly. Fun, different, keeps them entertained  and they can watch it over and over if they do have 2 hours to kill.
Excellent!!!

My children loved these.

Excellent movie! Presented just like it was on TV with "The Sneetches" first, "The Zax" second and "Green Eggs and Ham" last. I have all the Dr. Seuss blu-rays and this is one of my all-time favorites.  I really love "The Sneetches" and what it teaches.  Great movie; and, boy, does the movie look good on blu-ray!

This is the same cartoon from when I grew up in the 80's, with that 70's music and Chuck Jones Looney Tunes style we all remember and love... sigh. The only thing this nit-picky mother of an almost 4 year old preschooler can negatively say about this is that the word "stupid" is said. Of course, my son picked up on it immediately and although we had previously mentioned we didn't like that word being said, how can we tell him not to say it when we let him watch this cartoon? Other than that, I recognize it's a small negative detail in an otherwise wonderful (nostalgic) story, especially the message the Sneetches contains.
This DVD arrived in the mail in a timely manner, works perfectly, and my summer school students loved watching!

I teach Kindergarten, and every year for St. Patrick's Day we do Green Eggs & Ham day. This is my  favorite rendition of Green Eggs and Ham because the illustrations and the text stick to the book.

I teacher preschoolers with Autism...this DVD is a HUGE HIT!!! The animation is superb and the story follows the book version that we use in the classroom.  The DVD includes two other Dr. Seuss stories and captivate the students.  I HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT!
A great way to teach reading to your 2 and three year old. Use green food coloring and get your picky child to eat anything!
I love Dr seuss and still feel that the cartoon movies are the best the price was great and now my movie collection feels complete.

This is a classic and we wanted to be able to read the book and then see the movie.  Kids love to read the book with the movie.

My 10 year old, 8 year old, 2 year old and I all laughed and laughed.  In addition, the stories all are good for sparking conversations.  These are the classic, real thing.  We can't stand the new Martin Short voice on the Cat And The Hat series on PBS.  YUCK!  These are so much better.  Classic, clever and hilarious.
